-- HSBC Hires Deutsche Bank's Ben Katz to Oversee U.S. High-Grade Debt Unit
-- Sonja Cheung
-- 2010-06-15T09:42:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/hsbc-hires-deutsche-bank-s-ben-katz-to-oversee-u-s-high-grade-debt-unit.html

          
          
             HSBC Holdings Plc  said it hired
Deutsche Bank AG’s  Ben Katz  as head of financial investment-
grade debt markets for the U.S.  
 Katz will be based in New York and report to  Rob Gelnaw ,
HSBC’s head of debt capital markets for North America, the
London-based bank said in an e-mail. Katz, who will oversee debt
origination for U.S. institutions, will also co-head HSBC’s
financing solutions group for the Americas with  Matt Riez .  
 At Deutsche Bank in London, Katz advised European financial
companies on capital and liability management, according to the
statement.  
